Home > Visit > Things to Do

Things to Do This Summer












			May 26 - September 4, 2017

			From romantic escapes to fast-paced fun, the tempo of a Biltmore® summer keeps perfect time with longer days and leisurely pursuits. Kids 16 and under are admitted free, and with a glorious 8,000-acre Blue Ridge Mountain backyard to explore, families are invited to make the most of “together time.” Inside America’s largest home, grand rooms filled with masterpieces recall the graceful rhythm of Vanderbilt hospitality. With so much to do and see, and special savings at Biltmore’s two hotels, there’s no better time to experience Biltmore as it was originally intended: as an overnight guest.

			Your estate admission includes access to Antler Hill Village and Winery, featuring:


				Complimentary wine tastings at America’s Most Visited Winery

				Seasonal farm-to-table dining at your choice of three fantastic restaurants

				A variety of shops filled with unique Biltmore treasures

				Friendly farm animals to cuddle at our Farmyard

				The Outdoor Adventure Center, headquarters for estate exploration

				Our exhibition Fashionable Romance: 60 Years of Vanderbilt Family Wedding Fashion

				Intricate toy brick replicas of Biltmore House and the Lodge Gate

				A 250-foot model train display of George Vanderbilt’s railway travels


Save $10 on each admission ticket when you book 7+ days in advance! 

Buy Tickets                 Stay on Biltmore Estate








	More to Do





			Antler Hill Village & Winery

			Antler Hill Village® is the perfect place to unwind after a busy day on the estate, where you can enjoy live music daily, and opportunities to relax with the refreshment of your choice, whether that’s a glass of wine, an ice-cold beer, or an ice cream cone. Browse our shops, enjoy a meal at one of our restaurants, savor award-winning vintages at our Winery’s newly renovated indoor/outdoor wine bar, or pay a visit to our Farmyard to pet the friendly farm babies.

Learn More
Daily Live Music at the Antler Hill Village Bandstand
Live After Five Music Schedule
Events on the Estate this Summer














			Tours and Outdoor Activities

			Engaging tour opportunities include behind-the-scenes tours of Biltmore House and the estate, and special tours and tastings at our Winery. For those interested in exploring more of Biltmore’s 8,000 acres, our Outdoor Adventure Center provides an abundance of outdoor pursuits, from biking, horseback riding, and carriage rides, to Segway tours and Land Rover off-road driving, and such river-based options as float trips, kayaking, and stand up paddle boarding.

See All Tours
See Outdoor Activities








			Dining

			Summer means fresh flavors from Biltmore’s gardens and local farms, ranging from tender lettuces and asparagus to estate-raised lamb and artisan cheeses from area producers. Talented estate chefs take the season’s bounty to devise menus that pair perfectly with Biltmore’s award-winning wines, signature cocktails, and craft beers. Summertime holidays add expanded offerings for brunch, lunch, afternoon tea, and dinner across the estate.

Find Your Restaurant
























