Home > Events & Activities > Newsboys with Special Guest Mandisa

Newsboys with Special Guest Mandisa






			Welcomed by 106.9 The Light

			Friday, August 18

7:30 p.m. on Biltmore's South Terrace

			The Newsboys have defined contemporary Christian music for more than two decades. Moving fluidly between rock and pop, worship and dance, their live shows exhibit a kind of energy that, if it could be bottled, would power entire cities. Along the way, they’ve sold more than 8 million albums and amassed eight Gold® certifications, 33 #1 hits, four Grammy® nominations, two American Music Award nominations, and multiple Dove Awards. Additionally, their chart-topping, Platinum®-certified single, “God’s Not Dead,” inspired the 2014 hit film of the same name.

			With a strong, supple voice that is equally commanding on an up-tempo anthem or a tender ballad, contemporary Christian singer and songwriter Mandisa has developed a devoted legion of fans who appreciate not only her vocal gift but the heart that fuels her music. Following a top-ten finish on American Idol, Mandisa released her debut album True Beauty in 2007, earning the first of three Grammy® nominations. Her Grammy-winning fourth album Overcomer includes intensely personal singles including “Press On,” “Face to Face,” and What Scars Are For.” Her latest album Out of the Dark will be released in May 2017.

