Goo Goo Dolls: Long Way Home Summer Tour 2017 with special guest Phillip Phillips | Biltmore



















































Skip navigation








Home > Events & Activities > Goo Goo Dolls: Long Way Home Summer Tour 2017 with special guest Phillip Phillips

Goo Goo Dolls: Long Way Home Summer Tour 2017 with special guest Phillip Phillips






			Saturday, August 26

7:30 p.m. on Biltmore's South Terrace

			The Goo Goo Dolls have become one of the most globally respected and influential forces in popular music history, selling more than 10 million albums since 1986. In addition to a string of #1 and Top 10 singles including “Name,” “Slide,” and “Let Love In,” their hit “Iris,” from the City Of Angels soundtrack, was #1 on the Billboard charts for 17 consecutive weeks. During their career, the four-time Grammy nominees have toured the globe countless times and recorded and released 11 studio albums. Their newest EP is You Should Be Happy.

			Since releasing his five-times-platinum debut single “Home” in 2012, Phillip Phillips has put out two chart-topping albums and taken his earthy but expansive brand of guitar-fueled rock to stages across the globe. Featuring his rich, soulful vocals and ruggedly warm sensibilities, Phillips’ first album The World from the Side of the Moon went platinum soon after its debut. Two years later, his second album Behind the Light offered up the lead single “Raging Fire,” a major radio hit that revealed his bold twist on anthemic folk-rock.










