Lindsay Voitik
Lindsay Voitik is a native of Arizona and a graduate of Corona del Sol High School in Tempe.  She currently brings over 15 years of industry experience to Biltmore Wealth Management.
Lindsay began her career in 2000 with Charles Schwab, as a Transfer of Assets (TOA) Administrator, supporting RIA firms in her region.  During her 5 years at Schwab, Lindsay earned Schwab’s prestigious Presidents Award, for client service excellence.
In 2005, Lindsay began working for an RIA firm in Denver, Colorado, as a Client Service Associate and Operations Manager.  During her six-year tenure with the firm, Lindsay made significant contributions to its steady growth.
In 2011, Lindsay temporarily left the industry to start a family.  Then three years later, Lindsay’s family relocated back “home” to Arizona.  In January 2015 Lindsay re-entered the industry and brought her wealth of knowledge and experience to Biltmore Wealth Management.  She is currently their Client Service Associate, among many other “hats” she wears for the firm.  Biltmore Wealth Management feels fortunate to have such a valuable team member.
Lindsay currently resides in Anthem, Arizona with her husband Ryan and three kids, Rawley, Dawson and Kaylie.  Besides spending time with her family, Lindsay enjoys photography, hiking and traveling.
 

Client Service Associate 
Lindsay Voitik
